message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a novel approach for automatic left ventricle quantification using convolutional neural networks (CNN) and deep learning architectures. The paper focuses on medical image analysis and cardiovascular magnetic resonance datasets, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper introduces new deep learning architectures and optimization objective functions, which further supports the likelihood of belonging to these sub-categories. The paper also discusses the physiological measures of the left ventricle, indicating a potential fit for the medical informatics (cs.MED) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning in the paper suggests a possible fit for the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NEURON) sub-category.
